issues.title: Access control vulnerability
issues.description: The function `IamMissing()` is intended to be the constructor but has the wrong name. This means that anyone can call `IamMissing()` and overwrite the owner, leading to unauthorized access and potential compromise of the contract.
issues.debug: Anyone can call IamMissing() and change the owner

issues.title: State change after external call
issues.description: The function `withdraw()` transfers the contract's balance to the owner. If the owner is a contract, this call could trigger a reentrancy vulnerability if the fallback function of the owner contract calls back into this contract before the `transfer()` call completes. This could lead to unexpected behavior or potential loss of funds if the contract state is modified in the fallback function.
issues.debug: External call to owner followed by no state change
